# Cloudflare Pages headers for the WebCLAP demo.
#
# WebCLAP needs cross-origin isolation: the module imports a shared
# WebAssembly.Memory (threads + SharedArrayBuffer), which the browser only
# permits when the page is crossOriginIsolated. That requires BOTH of these on
# the DOCUMENT response:
#   Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
#   Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
#
# COEP: require-corp then BLOCKS any subresource that does not explicitly opt in
# via CORP (or CORS). So EVERY subresource — the .mjs modules, the .wasm, and
# any future font/image/worklet — carries Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy. The
# `/*` block below applies COOP/COEP/CORP to every response (document AND
# subresource); the per-extension blocks pin the correct MIME so the browser
# accepts the ES modules (text/javascript) and instantiates the module
# (application/wasm). This mirrors the working dev server, browser-host/serve.mjs.

/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

/*.wasm
  Content-Type: application/wasm

/*.mjs
  Content-Type: text/javascript; charset=utf-8

/*.js
  Content-Type: text/javascript; charset=utf-8

/*.css
  Content-Type: text/css; charset=utf-8
